cs.CL, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.CY, cs.HC 

This paper deals with natural language processing (NLP) techniques applied to electronic health records (EHRs) to extract descriptions of patient mobility. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CL (Computation and Language), which deals with NLP and its applications. The paper also discusses the use of recurrent neural networks (RNNs) and word embeddings, which are techniques commonly used in machine learning and deep learning, suggesting that cs.LG (Machine Learning) is also a likely category. Additionally, the paper discusses domain adaptation techniques, which are used to adapt models trained on one domain to another domain, suggesting that cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) is another likely category. The paper also deals with the challenges of extracting information from EHRs, which is a topic relevant to cs.CY (Computers and Society) and cs.HC (Human-Computer Interaction).
